==English==
===Alternative spellings===
* [[Ibrahim]]

===Etymology===
From the Greek [[Αβραάμ]] (Avraám), through Late Latin; from the Hebrew [[אברהם|אַבְרָהָם]] ('Abrāhām). Possibly compounded from [[אב|אָב]] (av = 'father') + [[המון]] (hamon = 'multitude') : father of a multitude or nations. Abram, Hebrew [[אברם|אַבְרָָם]], 'high father', from [[אב|אָב]] (av = 'father') + [[רם|ְַרָָם]] (ram = 'high').

===Proper noun===
'''Abraham'''

# A male [[given name]] of biblical origin.
# A prophet in the [[Old Testament]]; Semitic archfather, father of the Jewish archfather [[Isaac]] (by his wife [[Sarah]]) and the Arabic archfather [[Ishmael]] (by his concubine [[Hagar]]).

